Business Brief -- United Technologies Inc.:
   Photonics Subsidiary Formed
   After 10 Years of Research
The new unit capitalizes on more than 10 years of work in
the company's research center. The new unit, with more than
30 employees, will be moved to Bloomfield, Conn. United
Technologies, which is based in Hartford, Conn., didn't
disclose sales of the operation.
   Photonics has applications in fiber optics, including
optical navigation systems, cable television signal
distribution, antenna interconnects, telecommunications and
instrumentation.
   United Technologies provides a broad range of
high-technology products and support services to the
aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.